"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-uswnt-cruises-past-zambia-open-paris-olympics-group-stage\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The U.S. women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s national team shook off any lingering Olympic bitterness, defeating Zambia 3\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00930 in its first outing of the Paris Games on Thursday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 87, \"end\": 93, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.181113663364835e-13, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After disappointing appearances in the Tokyo Olympics and the 2023 World Cup, the U.S. needed to set the tone with a powerful statement out of the gates.\", \"from\": 152, \"to\": 305, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Nice, the team did just that.\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 309, \"end\": 313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OGC_Nice\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.16936306399378e-15, \"text\": \"Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OGC_Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OGC_Nice\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a sturdy performance from a young USWNT group eager to carve out a fresh identity under new coach Emma Hayes, who has only been with the squad since May.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve dreamed of this moment since I was a little girl,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Hayes told media ahead of Thursday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s game.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 380, \"end\": 385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USWNT\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 444, \"end\": 454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Hayes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTo be leading the U.S. team out to our first Olympic Games together is something I don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think I can put into words.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The Group B opener was not only an Olympic introduction for Hayes, but for many of her players as well.\", \"from\": 610, \"to\": 839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 740, \"end\": 747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\", \"score\": 0.9996989384142706, \"rank\": 0.00029971120654160736, \"text\": \"Group B\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Five first-time Olympians were featured in Hayes\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s starting lineup against Zambia, including Trinity Rodman, who wasted no time leaving her mark on the game, and the tournament.\\u00c2  Unleashing a barrage of quality shots on Zambia early, the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s opening few minutes were punctuated by a series of near misses.\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 1153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 917, \"end\": 923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.181113663364835e-13, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 935, \"end\": 949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinity_Rodman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Trinity Rodman\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinity_Rodman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinity_Rodman\"}, {\"begin\": 1063, \"end\": 1069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.181113663364835e-13, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It began to feel eerily familiar from the USWNT\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094plenty of dangerous chances created, but none converted.\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1260, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Enter Rodman, who opened the floodgates in a way only she could.\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1267, \"end\": 1273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Rodman\", \"score\": 0.9999999968567863, \"rank\": 2.783294162215184e-09, \"text\": \"Rodman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Rodman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Rodman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Streaking into the box in the 17th minute, Rodman got on the end of a well-weighted pass from Lindsey Horan before flicking the ball behind her to drop two defenders, then turning and striking a low shot behind Zambia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s goalkeeper.\\u00c2  THE USWNT IS OFF AND RUNNING.\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Rodman\", \"score\": 0.9999999968567863, \"rank\": 2.783294162215184e-09, \"text\": \"Rodman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Rodman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Rodman\"}, {\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Horan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lindsey Horan\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Horan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Horan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00ba\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b8Trinity Rodman with a tidy turn and finish to open the scoring against Zambia!#ParisOlympicspic.twitter.com/yyorSnoMSD  Rodman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s slick breakthrough started the party for the USWNT, which included back-to-back first-half goals from Mallory Swanson.\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1776, \"end\": 1781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USWNT\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1841, \"end\": 1848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\", \"score\": 0.9999999998590283, \"rank\": 8.113068366615819e-11, \"text\": \"Swanson\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a mere 66 seconds between her brace, Swanson now has the fastest two goals by a single player in a major tournament, according toOptaJack.\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1993, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1892, \"end\": 1899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\", \"score\": 0.9999999998590283, \"rank\": 8.113068366615819e-11, \"text\": \"Swanson\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening frame saw encouraging interplay between the fluid front line of Rodman, Swanson and Sophia Smith, at times linking up with ease.\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Rodman\", \"score\": 0.9999999968567863, \"rank\": 2.783294162215184e-09, \"text\": \"Rodman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Rodman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Rodman\"}, {\"begin\": 2078, \"end\": 2085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\", \"score\": 0.9999999998590283, \"rank\": 8.113068366615819e-11, \"text\": \"Swanson\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\"}, {\"begin\": 2090, \"end\": 2096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophia_Peletier\", \"score\": 0.9999989383464887, \"rank\": 1.0616402394445185e-06, \"text\": \"Sophia\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophia_Peletier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophia_Peletier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That trio, however, was broken up in the 40th minute when Smith exited the game for Lynn Williams after appearing to pick up a knock.\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2219, \"end\": 2232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lynn_Kanuka-Williams\", \"score\": 0.9981941818981296, \"rank\": 0.0018090849727349782, \"text\": \"Lynn Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lynn_Kanuka-Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lynn_Kanuka-Williams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Hayes said after the game that she doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have updates on Smith\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s status, but the 23-year-old will be assessed once the team is back at camp in Marseille.\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2419, \"end\": 2428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2283189429167695e-18, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \")\\u00c2  The substitutes kept coming in the second half, with Hayes showing she is not afraid to look down her bench.\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With the changes, Crystal Dunn, who started on the backline moved up the pitch to the wing, while Jenna Nighswonger, typically an outside back, joined the forward line.\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2640, \"end\": 2645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenna_Jameson\", \"score\": 0.7107230381731254, \"rank\": 0.4070168901734146, \"text\": \"Jenna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q488111\", \"Q483501\", \"Q33999\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenna_Jameson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenna_Jameson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This revealed another fundamental truth about Hayes's approach: a commitment to flexibility.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHaving a roster that could adapt is essential.\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We have a tight turnaround between games,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Hayes said after naming herOlympic rosterin June.\", \"from\": 2858, \"to\": 2952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSo of course, having players on the roster that could play more than one position mattered with squad depth.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Hayes\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s switches may help preserve players\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 legs in an action-packed Olympic tournament, but her moves also slowed the rhythm to finish out the game.\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 3222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. went scoreless in the second half, which isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t entirely surprising considering all the changes but will be something the team will likely want to amend going forward.\", \"from\": 3223, \"to\": 3400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the other side of the ball, the U.S. logged another clean sheet, which is no small feat against a lethal Zambia side.\", \"from\": 3402, \"to\": 3522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3510, \"end\": 3516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.181113663364835e-13, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Forward Barbra Banda, who Hayes called the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cmost in-form striker in world football,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d tested the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s backline, especially in transition.\", \"from\": 3523, \"to\": 3667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3531, \"end\": 3543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbra_Banda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbra Banda\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbra_Banda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbra_Banda\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Center back Naomi Girma, however, was up for the job, shutting down Banda in a trying, but ultimately uneventful 90 minutes.\", \"from\": 3668, \"to\": 3792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3736, \"end\": 3741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Banda_music\", \"score\": 0.7611195702476866, \"rank\": 0.31371428220798125, \"text\": \"Banda\", \"types\": [\"Q188451\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Banda_music\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Banda_music\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t the 2024 Olympic debut Zambia hoped for, competing with 10 players for the majority of the match after Pauline Zulu was issued a red card in the 30th minute.\", \"from\": 3793, \"to\": 3962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3828, \"end\": 3834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.181113663364835e-13, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3908, \"end\": 3915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pauline_Fowler\", \"score\": 0.9991868231167068, \"rank\": 0.000813838673245624, \"text\": \"Pauline\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pauline_Fowler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pauline_Fowler\"}, {\"begin\": 3916, \"end\": 3920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zulu_language\", \"score\": 0.9853923931019503, \"rank\": 0.014636286319362656, \"text\": \"Zulu\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zulu_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zulu_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s also worth noting that Zambia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s coach Bruce Mwape is not allowed private contact with any players at the Olympics, nor is he staying at the team hotel, due to anongoing investigation into sexual misconduct.\\u00c2  The U.S. now has two days\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 rest before facing off against a German side that looked completely dominant in its own 3\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00930 opening win over Australia.\", \"from\": 3963, \"to\": 4331, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4243, \"end\": 4249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.6904034125204501, \"rank\": 0.40870974165198865, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 4321, \"end\": 4330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5581228652546391, \"rank\": 0.7914659120283773, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hayes, however, has emphasized that every opponent deserves her team\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s utmost respect.\", \"from\": 4332, \"to\": 4420, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gone are the days of the USWNT cruising to the final, or even being considered a tournament favorite.\", \"from\": 4421, \"to\": 4522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4446, \"end\": 4451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USWNT\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAny given day any opponent can beat anyone,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Hayes.\", \"from\": 4523, \"to\": 4584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt has to be earned.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d With a forceful start, the U.S. showed it is, at the very least, up for the challenge.\\u00c2  Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 4585, \"to\": 4727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Clare Brennan is an associate editor for Sports Illustrated focused on women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sports.\", \"from\": 4728, \"to\": 4880, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4792, \"end\": 4797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clare_GAA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.594436792408403e-22, \"text\": \"Clare\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clare_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clare_GAA\"}, {\"begin\": 4798, \"end\": 4805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_J._Brennan_Jr.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0220991720306156e-14, \"text\": \"Brennan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_J._Brennan_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_J._Brennan_Jr.\"}, {\"begin\": 4833, \"end\": 4851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0887018430147768e-22, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before joining SI in October 2022, she worked as an associate editor at Just Women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Sports and as an associate producer for WDET in Detroit.\", \"from\": 4881, \"to\": 5024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5016, \"end\": 5023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Detroit\", \"score\": 0.994610845020712, \"rank\": 0.003937035423431295, \"text\": \"Detroit\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Detroit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Detroit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brennan has a bachelor\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in international studies from the University of Wisconsin and a master\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in art history from Wayne State University.\", \"from\": 5025, \